        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780571151462" href="/book/show/1456136.A_Minor_Apocalypse">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1670172204" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15515303559404002151">&quot;Day after day passes slowly. Lifes neck is ever longer. Everything&apos;s fucked as fucked as can be. We&apos;re not free, we&apos;re not free&quot; -b Set in the dying days of the PRL and inspired by the absurditites of life in the crumbling Polish State this surreal satire seems just as applicable to our world today. As with many of his Soviet Bloc contemporaries Tadeusz Konwicki demonstrates the inspiration provided by a political system that actively attempted to control thought and creativity. For me the book</span>
  <span id="freeText15515303559404002151" style="display:none">"Day after day passes slowly. Lifes neck is ever longer. Everything's fucked as fucked as can be. We're not free, we're not free" -b Set in the dying days of the PRL and inspired by the absurditites of life in the crumbling Polish State this surreal satire seems just as applicable to our world today. As with many of his Soviet Bloc contemporaries Tadeusz Konwicki demonstrates the inspiration provided by a political system that actively attempted to control thought and creativity. For me the book is a polemic against human stupidity (no one is free from assault in this work), it is unrelentingy grim and offers no real hope of salvation just odd moments of light in a world that is inevitably grey. At best ss one character says "We've given the oppressor the slip. We've outwitted him. We are free because we've imposed our own slavery".</span>
